x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Zeitschrift fuer Physik A, Hadrons and Nuclei, Vol.345, p.175 (1993)

x4freetext: -INTERACTION OF SLOW NEUTRONS WITH NUCLIDES OF SC, TI,
OPEN POOL REACTOR WITH THERMAL POWER OF 4MW,FRM
SLOW NEUTRONS (0.57MEV) WERE SCATTERED AT SMALL
A SET OF CONTINUOUSLY ROTATING DISKS OF RESONANCE
THE 1.26 EV AND 5.19EV NEUTRONS. THE MONO-ENERGETIC
NEUTRONS OF 18.6 EV AND 128 EV WERE SEPARATED IN A
TANGENTIAL BEAM TUBE BY THE RESONANCE SCATTERING TECH-
NIQUE USING W AND CO FOILS. A 1970 EV NEUTRON BEAM
WAS PRODUCED BY A RESONANCE SCATTER OF CU63 IN
COMBINATION WITH SE80 TARGET AND OTHER FILTERS.
.NATURAL AND ISOTOPICALLY ENRICHED TI, V AND MN AND SC
COMPOUNDS WERE USED. FOR TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENTS,
SOLID SAMPLES WERE USED. THE SOLID SAMPLES OF TI AND
V HAD A METALLIC PURITY OF 99.95 PERCENT (PC) AND
99.97 PC, RESPECTIVELY. THE TYPICAL HIGH IMPURITIES
OF SC SAMPLES WERE 3.3 WEIGHT PC W AND 2.2 PC
TA (FROM CONTAINERS). OTHER METAL IMPURITIES WERE LESS
THAN 1PC, LESS THAN 0.1PC FOR RARE EARTHS.
SAMPLES WERE HEATED TO 1700 K IN ULTRA HIGH VACUUM.
OR OTHER COMPOUNDS) WITH METALLIC PURITIES MORE THAN
SAMPLE WITHIN VARIOUS MIXTURES OF LIQUIDS WITH WELL
KNOWN SCATTERING DENSITY WERE USED. TRANSMISSION
MEASUREMENTS WERE ALSO CARRIED OUT TO DETERMINE THE
BF3 DETECTORS USED. NO DETAILS GIVEN.
